<h1>DotGNU Portable.Net Bugs and Patches</h1>
<p>
The bug tracker is
<a href="https://savannah.gnu.org/bugs/?group=dotgnu-pnet">here</a>
and the patch tracker is
<a href="https://savannah.gnu.org/patch/?group=dotgnu-pnet">here</a>.
</p>
<h2>Guidelines for submitting bugs and patches</h2>
<p>
<ul>
<li>Please be logged into Savannah when submitting a bug report or patch.</li>
<li>Please check the current open bugs to make sure that your bug hasn't
been reported already.</li>
<li>Please test with the current cvs version to make sure that your bug hasn't
been fixed already.</li>
<li>Bug reports should contain sufficient information to reproduce the
bug.</li>
<li>Please isolate the part of your program or library which doesn't work
properly because of the bug to a small test case, and attach that to your
bug report.</li>
<li>If the bug is easy to fix, please submit a patch which fixes it instead
of a bug report.</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h2>
 Your comments please...
</h2>
<p>
You are invited to add your comments concerning this page
at <a href="http://wiki.dotgnu.org/WebsiteComments/trackers">the appropriate
page of the DotGNU Wiki</a>
</p>
